cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.CC, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new dependent type theory that can be used as a logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses recursion and corecursion principles, which are important concepts in programming languages. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory and Logic) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new type theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper proves strong normalization of the reduction relation, which is a complexity property. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the definition of basic types and type formers.
